{
  "doc_id": "33498",
  "text": "As further confirmation of their viability, endothelial cells cultured within the microfluidic system appropriately expressed NO and VE-cadherin, as measured with 4,5-diaminofluorescein diacetate (DAF-2DA) fluorescence and immunofluorescence, respectively ( Figure 2 , A and B). Expression of NO is an integral part of endothelial function and requires the cells to be viable and functional [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Similarly, VE-cadherin expression occurred at endothelial cell junctions and was present throughout the entire inner surface in our endothelialized microdevices, providing further evidence the endothelial cells grossly achieve confluence in our system and are functioning appropriately [CITATION_3] .",
